---
<section id="contact" class="relative py-28 px-6 overflow-hidden">
  <div class="glow-blob w-[500px] h-[400px] bg-cyan/8 -bottom-20 right-0" style="position:absolute;"></div>

  <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="contact-card opacity-0 relative overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-white/8 bg-white/[0.03] p-12 md:p-16 text-center">
      <!-- Gradient border shimmer -->
      <div class="absolute inset-0 rounded-3xl pointer-events-none"
           style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(0,180,216,0.06) 0%, transparent 50%, rgba(99,102,241,0.06) 100%);"></div>

      <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Let's work together</p>
      <h2 class="section-title mb-5">
        Is your platform <span class="grad-text">misbehaving?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-white/50 leading-relaxed max-w-lg mx-auto mb-10 text-base">
        Should your cloud infrastructure find itself ensnared in an ossified tangle of
        artisanal snowflakes, nocturnal incident alerts, and the sort of undocumented
        tribal wisdom that evaporates with its last custodian — I entertain select
        engagements. Whether the affliction manifests as a recalcitrant EKS migration,
        a Terraform estate of considerable ambiguity, a GitOps workflow that has yet to
        discover Git, or a security posture best characterised as optimistic, I approach
        each pathology with the same diagnostic rigour. The more labyrinthine the
        problem, the more intellectually stimulating the consultation.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:nitin.solna@gmail.com"
         class="inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 px-8 py-3.5 rounded-xl font-semibold text-sm text-black transition-all duration-200 hover:scale-105 active:scale-95"
         style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00B4D8, #6366f1);">
        Start a conversation
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-white/6 flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4 text-white/30 text-xs font-mono">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-5 gap-y-2 justify-center md:justify-start items-center">
        <span>📍 Stockholm, Sweden</span>
        <a href="mailto:nitin.solna@gmail.com" class="hover:text-cyan transition-colors">nitin.solna@gmail.com</a>
        <a href="tel:+46730787990"             class="hover:text-cyan transition-colors">+46 730 787 990</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/nitinjain999" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:text-cyan transition-colors">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nitinjain999/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:text-cyan transition-colors">LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
      <span class="flex-shrink-0">© 2026 Nitin Jain</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  import { gsap } from 'gsap';
  import { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger';

  let ctx: gsap.Context | undefined;

  function init() {
    ctx?.revert();
    ctx = gsap.context(() => {
      gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);
      gsap.fromTo('.contact-card',
        { opacity: 0, y: 40 },
        { opacity: 1, y: 0, duration: 0.7, scrollTrigger: { trigger: '#contact', start: 'top 80%' } });
    });
  }

  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', init);
</script>
